On International Holocaust Remembrance Day, the President acknowledges the significance of this day and joins people worldwide in commemorating the Holocaust. The President emphasizes the importance of remembering the victims of the Nazis' hate, including six million Jews and millions of others. He also highlights the need to remain vigilant against the possibility of genocide and to ensure that "Never Again" is not just a phrase but a principled cause. The President calls for standing up against prejudice, stereotyping, and violence, including anti-Semitism. He also recognizes the brave individuals who risked their lives to save others during the Holocaust, demonstrating the capacity for compassion and justice even in the midst of evil. Lastly, the President pays tribute to the survivors, highlighting their faith, courage, and resilience in building lives of purpose and meaning. He urges the building of a more peaceful, just, and tolerant world in honor of those who were lost.